{
  "text": "even in normal rat or mouse heart, 3,76 the same is not true for the human ventricle. [CITATION_1] Here, the b 2 AR couples to cAMP production as strongly or even more strongly than b 1 AR 78 and phosphorylation of phospholamban, which is not observed in the rodent heart after b 2 AR stimulation, is equal to that produced by the b 1 AR. [CITATION_2] In the failing human heart, however, the bAR response is restored by PTX treatment, implying a Gi-mediated component to desensitization.",
